modules.description: Handles project configuration and build automation for OCaml projects by parsing and executing build rules, managing dependencies, and compiling source files. Operates on OCaml source files, libraries, and project metadata stored in configuration files. Used to streamline the build process for applications and libraries, ensuring consistent and reliable compilation across environments.

The module provides functions for equality checks, comparisons, hashing, pretty-printing, and string conversion of dynamic values, alongside builders for constructing units, primitives, tuples, lists, arrays, options, and opaque values. It supports creating structured data types like records, variants, and results via a builder pattern, encapsulating diverse inputs into a unified type. This enables flexible handling of heterogeneous data in scenarios such as serialization, configuration parsing, or runtime type manipulation.
